revision.text:
The '''adjutative voice''' is a [[grammatical voice]] carrying the meaning "to help to". The [[subject (grammar)|subject]] of a verb in the adjutative voice is not an [[agent (grammar)|agent]] of the action denoted by the verb, but assists the (unstated) agent in performing the action.
==References== *{{cite book | first = R. L. | last = Trask | year = 1993 | title = A Dictionary of Grammatical Terms in Linguistics | publisher = Routledge | isbn = 0-415-08628-0 }}
