'''Al-Bakbuk''' is an [[impact crater]] in the northern hemisphere of [[Saturn]]'s moon [[Enceladus (moon)|Enceladus]].  Al-Bakbuk was first observed in ''[[Cassini-Huygens Mission|Cassini]]'' images during that mission's March 2005 flyby of Enceladus.  It is located at {{Coord|5.65|N|191.19|W|globe:enceladus_source:gpn|notes=<ref name=gpn/>}} and is 9 kilometers across.  Since the crater's formation, numerous north-south trending fractures cut across the crater, forming canyons several hundred meters deep along the crater's rim.

Al-Bakbuk is named after one of the barber's six brothers in "[[The Hunchback's Tale]]" in ''[[The Book of One Thousand and One Nights]]''.

